In Yandex Cloud need to set root password: login as regulr user, and user passwd root
===
sudo tee /etc/profile.d/tweaker.sh <<'EOF'
# set TWEAKER for all users
export TWEAKER=postgres
EOF
===
sudo chmod 644 /etc/profile.d/tweaker.sh
===
reboot
echo $TWEAKER
# you should see: postgres
===
sudo sh -c 'echo "TWEAKER=postgres" >> /etc/environment'
===
sudo dnf install unixODBC unixODBC-devel
sudo dnf install postgresql-odbc
===
/etc/odbcinst.ini:
[PostgreSQL_TC_x64]
Description = ODBC version 12.00 for PostgreSQL
Driver      = /usr/lib64/psqlodbcw.so
Driver64    = /usr/lib64/psqlodbcw.so
FileUsage   = 1

===
1. Create the three data dirs
mkdir -p /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_idata \
         /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_indx \
         /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_ilog

2. Give them to the postgres process user
chown -R postgres:postgres /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_*

3. Secure with user-only write permission
chmod 777 /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_*
===
1.Create required directories
sudo mkdir -p /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_idata \
             /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_indx \
             /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_ilog

2.Change ownership to the postgres OS user
sudo chown postgres:postgres /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_idata \
                             /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_indx \
                             /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_ilog

3.Demo-only: allow all users read, write, and execute
sudo chmod 777 /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_idata \
               /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_indx  \
               /usr/Siemens/tcdb/infodba_ilog

sudo mkdir -p /usr/Siemens/tcpooldb/tcsrvmgr_idata
sudo chown -R postgres:postgres /usr/Siemens/tcpooldb/tcsrvmgr_idata
sudo chmod 777 /usr/Siemens/tcpooldb/tcsrvmgr_idata

===
for debug:
sudo dnf install lsof
sudo lsof -i :4544
sudo kill pid of the process uses 4544


